At work he’s recently reached the milestone of his 100th NRL game, with a career punctuated by representation at the international level, wearing the jerseys of the Cook Islands and New Zealand with pride. His exceptional performance, culminating in a Man of the Match award during the Kiwis' historic victory over the Kangaroos in the 2023 Pacific Championship final, underscores his significant impact on the sport. To book Charnze or to discuss your project, emailwork@liquorice.co.nzor click the link below and we’ll get back to you shortly.

Name: DAVE LETELE
Bio: Motivating people to become their best selves, one step at a time, New Zealand Local Hero of the Year Dave “Brown Buttabean” Letele is a true changemaker in his community and of his own circumstance. Coined “businessman to gangster, accountant to footy star, boxer to Samaritan”, Dave’s leadership journey started when he lost over 100 kgs and was inspired to help others achieve their goals. He has since founded The BBM Movement, a not-for-profit organisation that provides free fitness and nutrition coaching to people struggling with obesity or mental health issues. With street smarts and connections in droves, his power now goes far beyond these worthy topics as an intelligent, compassionate and considered ally to the underprivileged and the marginalised. Demanding credibility whether it be the boardroom or a gang funeral, his impact on the communities he serves is undeniable.

Following on from his many sporting strides and making use of his Bachelor of Applied Management and a Master of Professional Practice, learning and applying techniques on how to cultivate a strong culture and create a leadership framework are DJ’s reflections from his career that he is using to help build other high-performing businesses and teams through his coaching consulting. HANA TAPIATA PODCAST HANA TAPIATA FACEBOOK
